@startuml Sequence Diagram - Image Upload Flow
!theme cerulean-outline

title SmartMedia - Image Upload & Processing Sequence

actor User
participant "HomePage" as UI
participant "AppStore\n(Zustand)" as Store
participant "Electron\nMain" as Electron
participant "Processing\nQueue" as Queue
participant "Python\nEngine" as Python
participant "Qwen2-VL\nModel" as Model
participant "Face\nDatabase" as FaceDB
participant "SQLite\nDatabase" as DB

User -> UI: Click "Add Photos" button
activate UI

UI -> UI: Create file input\nelement

UI -> User: Show file picker dialog
User -> UI: Select image files
activate User

UI -> Store: setDiscoveredImages(filePaths)
activate Store

Store -> Store: Update discovered\nimages state

UI -> Store: setCurrentScreen('scanning')
Store -> Store: Update current screen

deactivate Store
deactivate User

UI -> UI: Navigate to\nScanningScreen

== Scanning & Processing Phase ==

UI -> Electron: processImage(imagePath)
activate Electron

Electron -> Queue: addTask(imagePath)
activate Queue

Queue -> Queue: Create ProcessingTask\n{id, path, status: 'queued'}

Queue -> Electron: Task queued
Electron -> UI: Queued successfully

Queue -> Python: {"action": "process_image",\n"path": imagePath}
activate Python

Python -> Python: Load image\nResize to 224x224

Python -> Model: Forward pass\n(vision-language inference)
activate Model

Model -> Model: Extract features\nGenerate embeddings

Model -> Python: Vision features
deactivate Model

Python -> Python: Extract:\n• Objects\n• Scene\n• Caption\n• Tags

Python -> Python: categorize_into_album()\nDetermine smart album

Python -> Python: detect_faces_in_image()
activate Python #LightBlue

Python -> FaceDB: Face detection\n& encoding
activate FaceDB

FaceDB -> FaceDB: Compare with\nexisting faces\n(distance < 0.6)

FaceDB -> FaceDB: Add or update\nface record

FaceDB -> Python: Face IDs &\nlocations
deactivate FaceDB
deactivate Python

Python -> Python: Compile AIResponse:\n{\n  caption, tags, objects,\n  album_category, faces\n}

Python -> Electron: JSON response
deactivate Python

Electron -> DB: saveImage(metadata)
activate DB

DB -> DB: INSERT INTO images\n(id, path, caption,\n tags, metadata, ...)"

DB -> Electron: Save successful
deactivate DB

Electron -> Store: addImages([imageMetadata])
activate Store

Store -> Store: Update images array\nTrigger re-render

Store -> UI: State updated
deactivate Store

UI -> UI: Update gallery view\nShow new image

deactivate Queue

alt More images in queue
  Queue -> Queue: Process next image
  note right: Repeat process for\neach queued image
else Queue empty
  Electron -> UI: processing:complete
  UI -> UI: Show completion\nmessage
end

deactivate Electron

User -> UI: View processed images\nin gallery
UI -> User: Display with AI-generated\ncaptions & tags

deactivate UI

note over User, DB
  **Processing Time**
  • First image: ~25-30s (model loading)
  • Subsequent: ~20-25s each
  • Background processing allows
    continued UI interaction
end note

note over Python, Model
  **AI Analysis Includes**
  1. Object detection (1000+ classes)
  2. Scene understanding
  3. Caption generation
  4. Tag extraction
  5. Face detection & recognition
  6. Emotion detection
  7. Album categorization
end note

@enduml
